---
import Layout from "../components/layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <header class="mb-12 border-b-4 border-black pb-8">
    <h1
      class="text-6xl md:text-8xl font-bold uppercase tracking-tighter leading-none mb-4"
    >
      Joining The<br />
      <span class="text-red-600">Webring</span>
    </h1>
  </header>

  <main class="max-w-4xl">
    <p class="text-2xl mb-12 font-medium">
      Joining the webring is super simple! Follow these steps:
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-12 text-xl">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold uppercase mb-4 flex items-center gap-4">
          <span class="w-6 h-6 bg-red-600 block shrink-0"></span>
          1. Fork the repo
        </h2>
        <div class="pl-10">
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            Start by forking the repository on GitHub by clicking on
            <a
              href="https://github.com/hackclub/webring/fork"
              class="text-red-600 underline font-bold hover:bg-red-600 hover:text-white transition-colors"
              >this link</a
            >. This creates a personal copy of the webring repository under your
            GitHub account, so you can update it freely.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold uppercase mb-4 flex items-center gap-4">
          <span class="w-6 h-6 bg-red-600 block shrink-0"></span>
          2. Add your site
        </h2>
        <div class="pl-10">
          <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Next, open the <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 text-sm font-bold"
              >src/members.json</code
            > file in your forked repository and add your site details in the following
            format at the end of the list:
          </p>
          <pre
            class="bg-black text-white p-6 font-mono overflow-x-auto shadow-sharp text-xl">
&#123;
  "member": "Your name here!",
  "url": "https://www.yoursite.com/"
&#125;</pre>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 italic text-lg">
            Then commit and push your changes to your forked repository.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold uppercase mb-4 flex items-center gap-4">
          <span class="w-6 h-6 bg-red-600 block shrink-0"></span>
          3. Submit a Pull Request
        </h2>
        <div class="pl-10">
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            Once your changes are pushed, go to the original repository and open
            a
            <a
              href="https://github.com/hackclub/webring/compare"
              class="text-red-600 underline font-bold hover:bg-red-600 hover:text-white transition-colors"
              >Pull Request</a
            >. The maintainers will review your addition, and once merged,
            you're officially part of the ring!
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold uppercase mb-4 flex items-center gap-4">
          <span class="w-6 h-6 bg-red-600 block shrink-0"></span>
          4. Embed the Ring
        </h2>
        <div class="pl-10">
          <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Finally, add the webring to your site! Paste this snippet into your
            HTML where you want the navigation to appear. It will automatically
            detect your domain and link to your neighbors.
          </p>
          <pre
            class="bg-black text-white p-6 font-mono text-xl overflow-x-auto shadow-sharp">
&lt;iframe
  src="https://webring.hackclub.com/embed"
  width="150"
  height="50"
  frameborder="0"
  scrolling="no"
&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <a
        href="/"
        class="w-full justify-center flex border-4 border-black bg-yellow-300 px-8 py-3 font-bold hover:brightness-80 transition"
      >
        Go Home
      </a>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
